{"title": "Unsanitized user input in HTTP request (SSRF)", "summary": "  Applications should not connect to locations formed from user input. This rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not connect to locations formed from user input.\nThis rule checks for URLs containing user-supplied data.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using user input in HTTP URLs:\n\n```ruby\nFaraday.get(\"https://#{params[:host]}')\n```\n\n\u2705 Use user input indirectly to form a URL:\n\n```ruby\nhost =\n  case params[:host]\n  when \"option1\"\n    \"api1.com\"\n  when \"option2\"\n    \"api2.com\"\n  end\n\nFaraday.get(\"https://#{host}')\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-918"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_lang_http_url_using_user_input"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}